Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; amphora symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.132, 2. A parallel is Cairo CG26092 (Milne 1905, 125); there is no good evidence that there are stamps from Naukratis excavations in Cairo, and so this is unlikely to be the same piece, even if the type is not otherwise attested.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1413)
